properties.areaDesc: Upper North Platte River Basin; Southwest Carbon County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 6 at 3:21AM MST until February 8 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MAJOR SNOW STORM CONTINUES THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING FOR THE
MOUNTAINS...

...SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW RETURNS TO THE INTERSTATE 80 CORRIDOR
BETWEEN RAWLINS AND PINE BLUFFS LATER TODAY THROUGH EARLY SATURDAY
MORNING...

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches, with locally higher amounts possible near the mountains.
Wind gusts up to 40 MPH at times.

* WHERE...Southwest Carbon County including Baggs and Dixon, Upper
North Platte River Valley including Saratoga.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Saturday. The worst conditions will occur
from late tonight through early Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be dangerous due to icy, snow covered
roads and periods of low visibility in falling and blowing snow.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST SATURDAY
